-- 
Lancashire Beats Somerset to Secure English County Cricket Championship

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-09-15T18:05:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/lancashire-beats-somerset-to-secure-english-county-cricket-championship.html
Lancashire defeated Somerset by
eight wickets to clinch its first outright English cricket
County Championship title since 1934.  The victory, combined with Warwickshire’s draw with
Hampshire, gave Lancashire the championship. Stephen Moore top-
scored with 71 as Lancashire, chasing 211 to win, reached 213-2
at Taunton.  Paul Horton scored 55 and Steven Croft was 40 not out.
Peter Trego scored 120 in Somerset’s second-innings 310 all out.  Lancashire shared the title with Surrey in 1950.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bob Bensch in  London  at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 